<br>
No, I dont think pet hold should be default.  Part of the challenge of the class is learning when/how to use a pet.<br>
<br>
Sometimes pets are great and cause no problems..<br>
Sometimes pets shouldn't be around at all...<br>
Sometimes you summon during the battle...<br>
<br>
I look at pet hold as a reward for alot of time invested in the class (time I'll never invest because I'm a committed rogue).  Anyway, it represents to me total mastery of the pet, which should be the result of a career spent learning about it...<br>
<br>
When I play the necro honeslty I dont care if I have a pet or not, good necros who really learn the class offer much more to a group than a skeleton on a string...  <br>
